Package: SoRE
Type: Package
Title: Annotation-Ranked Bayesian Fine-Mapping of GWAS Signals
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Siyi", family = "Chen",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "sche11@lsuhsc.edu",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000"))
Description: Implements SoRE (Sum of Ranked Effects), a Bayesian fine-mapping
    prior that encodes functional annotations through a Plackett-Luce
    distribution on variant orderings, and V-SoRE, an empirical-Bayes
    variational implementation that wraps SuSiE-RSS in an outer reweighting
    loop. The method localizes causal variants within GWAS-identified regions
    using GWAS summary statistics and external functional annotation, with a
    locus-specific variance parameter that controls fidelity to the annotation
    ordering and reverts to SuSiE-RSS when annotation and data disagree.
